                    <li>Eat-in warungs for delicious Balinese food at rock-bottom prices where delectable dishes are served in very warm atmospheres. </li>
                    <li>Discover the art scene of Ubud or enjoy a performance of traditional Kecak dance to taste culture.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>3. Prague, Czech Republic: A Fairy-Tale Romance on a Budget</h2>
                <p>Prague’s ageless charm, with its cobbled streets and historic architecture, gives romanticism a magical setting. Dubbed the “City of a Hundred Spires,” it is affordable for couples on a Eurotrip honeymooning together.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Book budget rooms around Old Town to eat hearty Czech meals in traditional pubs. Stroll hand-in-hand across Charles Bridge or climb Petrin Hill for breathtaking views of the city. </li>
                    <li>Visit Prague Castle and discover the multi-coloured Lennon Wall, as well as roaming in the beautiful streets of MalaStrana—all without smashing a piggy bank. </li>
                    <li>Free walking tours give you an in-depth look at the history and culture of the city. Transport all around the city is very efficient with detailed low fares. From FaresMatch, low-cost flight fares for Prague are easy to find, making fairy-tale destinations accessible to everyone. </li>
                    <li>Be it watching the chime of the Astronomical Clock or listening to the love songs by the Vltava River sunsets, Prague is the real winner for romance on a budget.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>4. Tulum, Mexico: Boho-Chic Love by the Sea</h2>
                <p>The beautiful beaches, cerulean waters, and a lovely bohemian aura of Tulum make it a romantic getaway, but fortunately, it is one of those destinations where the couple can afford the log hut.</p>
