                    <li>Enjoy true tacos and fresh ceviche without scrimping on taste and find out where it’s served on the street from stalls. </li>
                    <li>A day visiting these Mayan ruins facing the sea or snorkelling in clear cenotes like Dos Ojos or Gran Cenote is a great way to spend the day. </li>
                    <li>Enjoy some time at the public beaches in Tulum so you can soak in the amazing ocean scenery without having to pay for it at all. Rent bikes to navigate the area at a low cost and in an eco-friendly fashion.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>5. Budapest, Hungary: Become a Spa City for Romantic</h2>
                <p>Budapest—the “Spa Capital of the World”—is” a striking feature, balancing history and relaxation with romance.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>It is a prime city for couples where you can visit a few of the famous thermal baths—Szechenyi and Gellert spas—where you can have a few moments of soaking in the healing waters at a very reasonable price. </li>
                    <li>Walk along the Danube River and take in the view of the Parliament Building and Buda Castle. The budget-friendly sunset river cruise is a great thing to do together. </li>
                    <li>Explore the historic streets of the Jewish Quarter, and indulge in some hearty traditional Hungarian food at little local bistros where you won’t break the bank. </li>
                    <li>Budget-friendly accommodation options near the centre are available, maximising walking or public transport access to all sites. From having a luxurious soak in the spa to a leisurely walk at the river, romance fills every corner of Budapest.</li>
